{
  "text": "In the present paper we deal with membranous proteins, the TM domains of which are shorthelices. These proteins comprise the major part of all integral membrane proteins across phyla (Liu et al., 2002) . A relatively small group of proteins that cross the bilayer membrane via a cluster of -sheets (e.g., porin) will not be considered [CITATION_1] .",
